bilingual.source: A farmer found an ancient sculpture on his land.
bilingual.target: 一个农民在他的土地上发现了古雕塑。

bilingual.source: That huge sculpture you can see is the Winged Victory of Samothrace.
bilingual.target: 你看到的那个巨大的雕塑是萨莫色雷斯的胜利女神。

bilingual.source: For example, in our free time we can sculpt a sculpture and paint a painting, but we take a photo.
bilingual.target: 例如，在空闲时间我们可以雕刻雕塑和画画，但我们拍照。

bilingual.source: The sculpture is made entirely of fer.
bilingual.target: 这座雕塑完全由铁制成。

bilingual.source: The sculptor spent months perfecting the details of the sculpture.
bilingual.target: 这位雕塑家花了几个月的时间完善雕塑的细节。
这座雕塑看起来像真人。

bilingual.source: The artist used wax to create a sculpture.
bilingual.target: 艺术家用蜡来创作雕塑。

bilingual.source: He made a sculpture out of metal plate.
bilingual.target: 他用金属板材做了一个雕塑。

bilingual.source: She admired the clean arris of the sculpture.
bilingual.target: 她欣赏雕塑干净的棱角。

bilingual.source: The artist created a sculpture using tin.
bilingual.target: 艺术家用锡制作了一件雕塑。

list.abstract: sculpture /ˈskʌlptʃə(r)/DJ /'skʌlptʃɚ/KK noun a work of art that is a solid figure or object made by carving or shaping wood, stone, clay, metal, etc. 雕像；雕塑品；雕刻品countableuncountable a marble sculpture of Venus 维纳斯的大理石雕像 He collects modern sculpture. 他收藏现代雕塑。 the art of making sculptures 雕刻术；雕塑术uncountable the techniques of sculpture in stone 石雕技艺 Derivative:sculpturaladjective /ˈskʌlptʃərəl/DJ /'skʌlptʃərəl/KK sculptural decoration 雕饰

yingyinNormal.en: I'm just glad I didn't go for the sculpture.
Or there's a sculpture park we could visit. Or there's... Ooh, there's wine tasting.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那儿还有个雕塑公园，我们可以去逛逛，还有个红酒品鉴会。

yingyinNormal.en: I picked up the earring. What? What's the earring? What are you guys talking about? The hot, sculpture, artist guy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我去取耳环了。什么？什么耳环？你们在说什么？那个火辣的雕塑家，艺术男。

yingyinNormal.en: So what'd you get the birthday boy? Well, Raj got him an awesome, limited edition dark knight sculpture based on Alex Ross's definitive batman.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们准备了什么生日礼物？拉杰给他买了一个特别赞的限量版黑暗武士的雕塑，是出自阿列克斯·罗丝版本授权的蝙蝠侠。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, yeah! Boy. Urine cuts right through an ice sculpture, doesn't it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，他小便时，直接喷中了冰雕，对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Casts of the same sculpture can be found in Belfast and Berlin, and it is simply called Reconciliation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 贝尔法斯特和柏林也都有这座雕像,它的名字就只有一个词，和解。

yingyinNormal.en: A reminder of what is possible when people reach out to one another, rather like the couple in the sculpture.
yingyinNormal.zh: 时时告诉人们，只要握手言和，繁荣就在眼前，就像雕像里的那对夫妇。

yingyinNormal.en: In the ruins of the old Coventry cathedral, is a sculpture of a man and a woman reaching out to embrace each other.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在考文垂大教堂遗迹之中，立着一座构型为男女相拥的雕像。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a work of art that is a solid figure or object made by carving or shaping wood, stone, clay , metal, or others

examination_example.sentence: She is proud that several <highlight>sculptures</highlight> have even gone on display again, albeit sometimes beneath protective cases.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她感到自豪的是，一些雕塑甚至再次展出，尽管有时是在保护壳下。

examination_example.sentence: So van Oosten and her colleagues worked to preserve Gilardi's <highlight>sculptures</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因此，范·奥斯滕和她的同事们致力于保护吉拉蒂的雕塑。

examination_example.sentence: Humans are unique in their capacity to not only make tools but then turn around and use them to create superfluous material goods — paintings, <highlight>sculpture</highlight> and architecture.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人类的独特之处在于，他们不仅能制造工具，而且还能利用它们创造多余的物质商品——绘画、雕塑和建筑。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a work of art that is a solid figure or object made by carving or shaping wood, stone, clay , metal, or others

examination_example.sentence: He builds massive <highlight>sculptures</highlight> out of plastic garbage, forcing viewers to re-examine their relationship to single-use plastic products.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他用塑料垃圾建造出了巨大的雕塑，使观众重新审视他们与一次性塑料产品的关系。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>sculpture</highlight> made its first appearance at the Estella Place shopping center in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这件雕塑首次出现在越南胡志明市的埃斯特拉广场购物中心。

examination_example.sentence: The Pompidou Centre in Paris is showing its respect for the artist with an exhibition bringing together over 200 paintings, <highlight>sculptures</highlight> and more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 巴黎蓬皮杜中心举办了一场展览，汇集了200多幅绘画、雕塑等作品，以表达对这位艺术家的尊重。
